## Responsive Design

### Breakpoints

```css
sm: 640px
md: 768px
lg: 1024px
xl: 1280px
2xl: 1536px
```

**Mobile-First Approach**: Default styles for mobile, progressively enhance

### Mobile Card Pattern

**Pattern**: Replace tables with cards on mobile

```typescript
{/* Desktop table */}
<div className="hidden md:block">
  <Table>...</Table>
</div>

{/* Mobile cards */}
<div className="md:hidden space-y-sm">
  {items.map(item => (
    <Card key={item.id}>
      <CardContent className="p-sm">
        {/* Card content */}
      </CardContent>
    </Card>
  ))}
</div>
```

**Breakpoints by Feature**:
- Livret A transactions: `md` breakpoint (768px)
- PEA holdings: `lg` breakpoint (1024px)
- PEE contributions: `md` breakpoint (768px)

**Why Different Breakpoints**: Based on data complexity and column count

### Responsive Navigation

**Desktop**: Sidebar always visible

**Mobile/Tablet**: 
- Sidebar hidden
- Hamburger menu shows Sheet component
- Sheet opens from left side

**Implementation**:
```typescript
{/* Mobile trigger */}
<Button className="lg:hidden" variant="ghost" size="icon">
  <Menu />
</Button>

{/* Desktop sidebar */}
<aside className="hidden lg:block">
  <Sidebar />
</aside>
```

