## Accessibility

### Color Contrast

**Goal**: WCAG 2.1 AA compliance

**Primary Text**: 4.5:1 minimum contrast ratio

**Large Text**: 3:1 minimum contrast ratio

**Tested**: Primary green meets contrast requirements

### Semantic HTML

**Always Use**:
- `<nav>` for navigation
- `<main>` for main content
- `<article>` for cards/sections
- `<button>` for interactive elements

**Never Use**:
- `<div>` with onClick (use `<button>`)
- Non-semantic wrappers when semantic options exist

### ARIA Labels

**Pattern**: Add labels for screen readers

```typescript
<Button aria-label="Close dialog">
  <X />
</Button>
```

**When to Use**: Icon-only buttons, complex interactions

